To calculate the Cash to Current Debt Ratio, use the formula:

\[
\text{Cash to Current Debt Ratio} = \frac{\text{Cash and Cash Equivalents}}{\text{Total Current Liabilities}}
\]

Step 1: Identify Cash and Cash Equivalents (at the end date 2024-02-02)  
Cash on Hand = 2,067,352.98  
Bank Deposits = 3,752,082.80  
Sum = 2,067,352.98 + 3,752,082.80 = 5,819,435.78

(Note: This matches the "Ending Balance" in cash flow section: 5,819,435.78)

Step 2: Identify Total Current Liabilities (end date 2024-02-02)  
Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91

Step 3: Calculate ratio:

\[
\frac{5,819,435.78}{7,605,149.91} \approx 0.765
\]

Rounded to two decimals: 0.77

So, the Cash to Current Debt Ratio is approximately 0.77.
